00:19:16.530 --> 00:19:20.040
So what is a payment system?

00:19:20.040 --> 00:19:23.450
Let's just dive in and
talk about what it is.

00:19:23.450 --> 00:19:26.760
And it's been around a century.

00:19:26.760 --> 00:19:28.830
So it's not a new thing.

00:19:28.830 --> 00:19:32.760
But in a digital world,
in a ledger-based world,

00:19:32.760 --> 00:19:37.170
it's a method to
change a ledger.

00:19:37.170 --> 00:19:38.670
Now, this isn't an
accounting class.

00:19:38.670 --> 00:19:40.420
I'm not going to bore
you with accounting.

00:19:40.420 --> 00:19:42.480
But basically, if I'm
moving money to you,

00:19:42.480 --> 00:19:47.910
somebody has to lower my
account, credit my account.

00:19:47.910 --> 00:19:50.680
Remember assets or debits.

00:19:50.680 --> 00:19:53.970
So credit means it's
going down, a little bit

00:19:53.970 --> 00:19:55.680
of accounting here.

00:19:55.680 --> 00:19:59.040
And then somebody else's
account has to be debited.

00:19:59.040 --> 00:20:01.350
So one debit, one credit.

00:20:01.350 --> 00:20:04.590
One account goes down,
one account goes up.

00:20:04.590 --> 00:20:09.630
It's also about authorizing
those movements and then

00:20:09.630 --> 00:20:12.270
what's called clearing
and final settlement.

00:20:12.270 --> 00:20:14.050
And earlier we discussed that--

00:20:14.050 --> 00:20:15.960
and sometimes final
settlement doesn't

00:20:15.960 --> 00:20:18.080
happen for a couple of days.

00:20:18.080 --> 00:20:21.660
And a long time ago, if
you wrote a physical check,

00:20:21.660 --> 00:20:23.610
you might not have
it settled, meaning

00:20:23.610 --> 00:20:29.310
having money in your account
for five days or longer even.

00:20:29.310 --> 00:20:32.270
Now it's closer to two days.

00:20:32.270 --> 00:20:36.000
But it's basically amending
and recording those ledgers.

00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:38.920
That's what it is in
an accounting system.

00:20:38.920 --> 00:20:40.780
And so how did we do this?

00:20:40.780 --> 00:20:43.550
This is just some
fun background,

00:20:43.550 --> 00:20:46.230
but Thomas Jefferson, the
writer of the Declaration

00:20:46.230 --> 00:20:49.680
of Independence, actually
you can find online a check

00:20:49.680 --> 00:20:50.890
he wrote to himself.

00:20:50.890 --> 00:20:53.370
I'm not quite sure why he did.

00:20:53.370 --> 00:20:56.420
This would have been the
year after he was president,

00:20:56.420 --> 00:20:58.230
but he wrote a check to himself.

00:20:58.230 --> 00:21:02.020
So physical personal checks
have been around a long time,

00:21:02.020 --> 00:21:04.540
but they are basically
an instruction

00:21:04.540 --> 00:21:06.930
called negotiable
orders of withdrawal,

00:21:06.930 --> 00:21:10.180
but an instruction to a
bank to amend the ledger.

00:21:10.180 --> 00:21:13.590
Lower my ledger, and
give me maybe paper cash,

00:21:13.590 --> 00:21:16.320
or lower my ledger,
raise somebody else's.

00:21:18.925 --> 00:21:20.800
All of the sudden, the
telegraph comes along.

00:21:20.800 --> 00:21:23.710
And a company, Western
Union, which still exists--

00:21:23.710 --> 00:21:28.210
Western Union comes along,
and it's a telegram company.

00:21:28.210 --> 00:21:32.260
But they figure out how to
send money by telegraph,

00:21:32.260 --> 00:21:34.450
the FinTech of its time.

00:21:34.450 --> 00:21:36.970
And yes, there were
machines that looked

00:21:36.970 --> 00:21:38.710
like this, telex machines.

00:21:38.710 --> 00:21:43.000
These were ubiquitous across
financial firms in the 1950s

00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:44.590
to the 1970s.

00:21:44.590 --> 00:21:47.830
I will admit I saw one or two of
these when I was on Wall Street

00:21:47.830 --> 00:21:50.020
still in the 1980s.

00:21:50.020 --> 00:21:53.710
But a telex machine
existed basically

00:21:53.710 --> 00:21:59.212
to send instructions on
payments around to another bank.

00:21:59.212 --> 00:22:01.680
