00:23:19.440 --> 00:23:22.460
and it might be
now $1.9 trillion.

00:23:22.460 --> 00:23:27.070
So it's gone up $100
billion or approximately.

00:23:27.070 --> 00:23:30.850
But the digital money, all the
people's bank accounts, bank

00:23:30.850 --> 00:23:34.990
deposits, money market funds
is multiples of that, $15

00:23:34.990 --> 00:23:37.300
or so trillion.

00:23:37.300 --> 00:23:41.350
So about 90% of the
money in the US,

00:23:41.350 --> 00:23:44.680
depending upon your definition
of money, is digital.

00:23:44.680 --> 00:23:47.950
And most of that digital money
is commercial bank money.

00:23:47.950 --> 00:23:49.870
You and I, when we
go into Starbucks,

00:23:49.870 --> 00:23:55.270
we're basically spending Bank
America dollars, or Citibank

00:23:55.270 --> 00:23:58.660
