this network, a point of sale--

00:27:22.870 --> 00:27:24.850
POS is point of sale--

00:27:24.850 --> 00:27:28.570
or by phone or by some
modern mechanism to access

00:27:28.570 --> 00:27:30.350
that network.

00:27:30.350 --> 00:27:34.430
And then the merchant
on the other side.

00:27:34.430 --> 00:27:38.830
So you have consumer
all the way to merchant.

00:27:38.830 --> 00:27:41.740
You have banks,
the issuing bank.

00:27:41.740 --> 00:27:44.880
The issuing bank is that
party that says, all right,

00:27:44.880 --> 00:27:48.250
I'm going to take a
payment instruction.

00:27:48.250 --> 00:27:50.650
And you have the merchant
bank on the other side

00:27:50.650 --> 00:27:53.310
or acquire a bank,
sometimes it's called.

00:27:53.310 --> 00:27:56.860
But in the middle,
there's some network.

00:27:56.860 --> 00:27:59.830
And it leads to a
lot of concentration

