00:28:44.440 --> 00:28:49.000
As a merchant, there's
a value to getting

00:28:49.000 --> 00:28:53.830
final settlement when
you sell your coffee

00:28:53.830 --> 00:28:57.520
or sell your produce or
a big machine, whatever

00:28:57.520 --> 00:28:59.660
you're selling.

00:28:59.660 --> 00:29:03.320
And there's the value
because there's certainty,

00:29:03.320 --> 00:29:04.790
and there's also timing.

00:29:04.790 --> 00:29:07.640
So if you can get your cash on
Monday rather than Wednesday,

00:29:07.640 --> 00:29:09.140
there's a value to it.

00:29:09.140 --> 00:29:12.830
Payment systems around
the globe historically

00:29:12.830 --> 00:29:16.670
could give you final settlement
if you used physical cash.

00:29:16.670 --> 00:29:20.720
And physical cash under the
laws of the developed world

00:29:20.720 --> 00:29:24.980
became final settlement
from the earliest days.

00:29:24.980 --> 00:29:27.740
There's a famous lawsuit
from the Crawford case,

00:29:27.740 --> 00:29:30.770
if you ever want to look it up,
about final settlement using

00:29:30.770 --> 00:29:31.670
physical cash.

00:29:31.670 --> 00:29:36.800
It's from the days of
King George II, I think.

00:29:36.800 --> 00:29:41.690
But digitally, it was harder
to get final settlement,

00:29:41.690 --> 00:29:43.830
and we still have delays.

00:29:43.830 --> 00:29:46.760
So what's happened
in the last 25

00:29:46.760 --> 00:29:49.100
years is many nations
have said, can we

00:29:49.100 --> 00:29:52.790
get to real-time
settlement rather

00:29:52.790 --> 00:29:55.760
than delayed settlement
of one day, two days,

00:29:55.760 --> 00:29:57.830
or, in the old days, five days?

00:29:57.830 --> 00:30:00.110
And trying to get to
that real-time settlement

00:30:00.110 --> 00:30:01.130
has been a challenge.

00:30:01.130 --> 00:30:03.660
And we'll go through different
countries in about a half

00:30:03.660 --> 00:30:04.160
an hour.

00:30:04.160 --> 00:30:05.450
Let me hold that.

00:30:05.450 --> 00:30:07.940
But a lot of countries,
central banks around the globe

00:30:07.940 --> 00:30:10.130
are trying to get to
real-time settlement.

00:30:10.130 --> 00:30:14.810
But the value is to the merchant
that they have finality,

00:30:14.810 --> 00:30:18.120
that they can then use
those funds in some way.

00:30:18.120 --> 00:30:21.210
And I can tell you, even when I
was the chief financial officer

00:30:21.210 --> 00:30:24.530
of the Hillary Clinton
campaign in 2016,

00:30:24.530 --> 00:30:25.490
we had to deal with it.

00:30:25.490 --> 00:30:28.760
We were the merchant
on the right-hand side.

00:30:28.760 --> 00:30:30.680
We might get a donation.

00:30:30.680 --> 00:30:34.690
But until that donation
actually settled,

00:30:34.690 --> 00:30:37.840
sometimes several days later,
sometimes a day later--

00:30:37.840 --> 00:30:40.120
it was different
settlement cycles--

00:30:40.120 --> 00:30:42.490
but until that settled,
we couldn't actually

00:30:42.490 --> 00:30:46.630
use it to buy advertisements
on, let's say,

00:30:46.630 --> 00:30:48.850
Facebook or Google Ads.

00:30:48.850 --> 00:30:51.790
So we needed-- even
in that instance,

00:30:51.790 --> 00:30:54.580
particularly when you get down
to the last six or 10 days

00:30:54.580 --> 00:30:58.150
before election time,
those days matter.

00:30:58.150 --> 00:31:00.580
So I lived this as a--

