00:41:57.030 --> 00:42:02.850
That's part of these pain
points is that fraud.

00:42:02.850 --> 00:42:07.260
Basically, when you think
of all the pain points,

00:42:07.260 --> 00:42:14.250
you and I, as users, we want
something that's easy to use,

00:42:14.250 --> 00:42:15.540
nearly costless.

00:42:15.540 --> 00:42:17.250
We're willing to
spend something,

00:42:17.250 --> 00:42:20.670
but we'd prefer not to spend
2% to 3% of our purchases

00:42:20.670 --> 00:42:22.650
on the payment system.

00:42:22.650 --> 00:42:26.310
And we want it not
to have complexity,

00:42:26.310 --> 00:42:30.210
the cross-border payments
that we talked about earlier.

00:42:30.210 --> 00:42:32.880
We kind of know that
they're tracking us,

00:42:32.880 --> 00:42:35.130
they're getting our data,
but we're a little concerned

00:42:35.130 --> 00:42:36.940
about data privacy.

00:42:36.940 --> 00:42:41.370
And so you're capturing one of
the pain points around fraud.

00:42:41.370 --> 00:42:43.510
And that's from
the merchant side.

00:42:43.510 --> 00:42:45.150
The merchant doesn't
want the fraud,

00:42:45.150 --> 00:42:46.500
but also you don't want it.

00:42:46.500 --> 00:42:50.460
You don't want somebody to be
able to tap into your account

00:42:50.460 --> 00:42:52.110
and move your money out.

00:42:52.110 --> 00:42:55.080
And the pain point sounds
like the fraud detection

00:42:55.080 --> 00:42:59.070
system that your bank is using
is requiring your mobile phone

00:42:59.070 --> 00:43:02.220
in a way that's friction.

00:43:02.220 --> 00:43:04.650
It's frankly friction.

00:43:04.650 --> 00:43:06.570
It's similar to a pain point--

00:43:06.570 --> 00:43:09.810
it used to be until
very recently,

00:43:09.810 --> 00:43:15.780
if you traveled overseas, you
were better to tell your bank

00:43:15.780 --> 00:43:19.620
that you were going to be using
your credit card in Spain,

00:43:19.620 --> 00:43:23.790
or France, or Asia, or Bahrain.

00:43:23.790 --> 00:43:27.890
But now no longer
because now they have--

00:43:27.890 --> 00:43:30.270
they use our mobile
phones to say--

00:43:30.270 --> 00:43:31.500
they track us.

00:43:31.500 --> 00:43:35.340
They know that we're in Spain,
or France, or Asia, or Bahrain.

00:43:35.340 --> 00:43:39.400
That's part of the reason we
don't need to call any longer,

00:43:39.400 --> 00:43:42.720
but that's part of their
fraud detection programs.

00:43:42.720 --> 00:43:46.710
Let me keep moving on if I can.

00:43:46.710 --> 00:43:48.630
So there's a series
of pain points.

00:43:48.630 --> 00:43:51.990
And I don't necessarily have all
of them, but these are also--

00:43:51.990 --> 00:43:55.270
you can think of them
as opportunities.

00:43:55.270 --> 00:43:58.350
These are opportunities
for disruptors to say,

00:43:58.350 --> 00:44:01.230
maybe we can provide
a better service.

00:44:01.230 --> 00:44:06.480
Maybe we can provide
something at a lower

00:44:06.480 --> 00:44:11.370
cost and more inclusive.

00:44:11.370 --> 00:44:16.090
These are the possibilities
for any startup in a sense.

00:44:16.090 --> 00:44:19.810
